UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407689900602
AB  - This paper alerts the potential applicant of the nonlinear two-stage least-squares (NL2S) estimator to a difficulty encountered in using the procedure to estimate a Box-Cox-transformed model. It points out that the estimator is not well defined when the untransformed dependent variables all exceed 1 or are all fractions. The problem is one of identification in the application of the NL2S estimator to the Box-Cox regression model.
